.include {_Setup.qd}

The **`.clip {shape}`** block function allows clipping its content to a defined shape.

Supported shapes:
- `circle`

```markdown
![Sky](sky.jpg)

.clip {circle}
    ![Sky](sky.jpg)
```

!(600)[Circle sky](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/f49dcb96-2e68-4cf7-94fd-71adad0072c7)



In case of a [figure](Figure.qd) only the content is affected, leaving its caption intact:

```markdown
![Sky](sky.jpg "A beautiful sky.".qd)

.clip {circle}
    ![Sky](sky.jpg "A beautiful sky.".qd)
```

!(600)[Circle sky figure](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/29b84532-d517-4857-a3c9-a70dfbea5a78)



